info: ['good condition macy‚Äôs cream beige l...', '$1,600.00', 'burbank, ca']
description:
Measurements: 138" on the longest side along the back, 97" on the second-longest side, and the chaise is 66".

My tan/cream/beige leather sectional that I bought brand new from Macy's 5-6 years ago used to fit perfectly in the space at my old house. However, the available downstairs space at my new house just does not suit this couch unfortunately (despite it being double the size of my old downstairs!!! It's just the layout). Consequently, I've been living with the couch both flipped "backwards" and also blocking a door leading to storage under the stairs. It has been quite a pain getting into the storage anytime we need something from it.

Given these problems, I've been looking to replace this sectional for a while, much as I love it. Well, I finally decided on a suitable replacement couch set! So I'm putting some feelers out to see how much this couch might still be worth. It was $4,000+ plus tax when I bought it new. 

It is showing some light signs of wear, but the only real flaws are that it does have a number of small cat scratches from when my two young cats were kittens, about 2 years ago. They used to chase each other around and the couch unfortunately became part of their obstacle course. I finally solved the problem with scat mats, and the couch has not sustained a new scratch ever since. I have the matching leather color from the manufacturer which can be used to periodically touch up these scratches, as needed. I would also recommend using a leather cleaner and conditioner on it, which will spruce the look of the leather right up again.

Pictures included are both from the old house (when the couch used to fit correctly in the space, so you can see what it's supposed to look like) and more recent pictures from my new house (how it looks today).. Make an offer!
